question: 一周
sourceMnemonic: <kanji>One</kanji> <kanji>circumference</kanji> is <vocabulary>one time around</vocabulary>. How many times will you go around the moon? Just <ja>一周</ja>?
sourceReadingMnemonic: This is a jukugo word, which usually means on'yomi readings from the kanji. If you know the readings of your kanji you'll know how to read this as well. Note that the <ja>いち</ja> becomes <ja>いっ</ja> as it often does when being used in a counter (<ja>一階</ja>, <ja>一回</ja>, etc.).
